HEADWORD: Extramural
<hw>Ex`tra*mu"ral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Outside of the walls, as of a fortified or walled city.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>pertaining to activities, such as sports contests,
that involve representatives from more than one school.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extraneity</ent>⟦br⟧
